# Cursor AI Configuration

This project uses a centralized AI configuration system located in the `.ai/` directory.

## Main Configuration

**Read and follow all guidelines in `.ai/agents.md`**

This file contains:
- Project overview and principles
- Coding standards and architecture guidelines
- Framework-specific rules
- Project conventions

## Key Documentation

### Core Rules
- `.ai/agents.md` - Root specification (start here)
- `.ai/guide.md` - How to use the AI config system

### Framework Rules
- `.ai/rules/coding-style.md` - General coding standards
- `.ai/rules/architecture.md` - System architecture patterns
- `.ai/rules/typescript.md` - TypeScript conventions
- `.ai/rules/nextjs-patterns.md` - Next.js best practices
- `.ai/rules/tailwind.md` - Tailwind CSS guidelines
- `.ai/rules/testing.md` - Testing standards
- `.ai/rules/security.md` - Security requirements

### Project Conventions
- `.ai/project/component-library.md` - Component patterns
- `.ai/project/api-patterns.md` - API design patterns
- `.ai/project/state-management.md` - State management approach
- `.ai/project/folder-structure.md` - Project organization

### Helpful Prompts
- `.ai/prompts/refactor.prompt.md` - Code refactoring templates
- `.ai/prompts/review.prompt.md` - Code review templates
- `.ai/prompts/test-generator.prompt.md` - Test generation templates
- `.ai/prompts/doc-writer.prompt.md` - Documentation templates

## When Coding

1. Check `.ai/agents.md` for project principles
2. Follow framework-specific rules in `.ai/rules/`
3. Use project conventions from `.ai/project/`
4. Reference prompt templates when needed

## Benefits

- Consistent code across the project
- Clear guidelines for all AI assistants
- Easy to maintain and update
- Portable configuration system
